        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 5:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " on account of unchaste looks, desires and lusts: giving offence to Christ's disciples, or endeavouring, by any means whatever, to cause them to stumble and fall, is equally gratifying the flesh, and no more to be indulged, than the other, on pain of eternal damnation. See Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 5:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 5:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
